# Skill Router

When a task matches a pattern below, **read the corresponding `SKILL.md` before starting** and complete the steps it defines (including the tests, route/OpenAPI registration, docs, and lint it lists) as part of the same change — see `agent-os/rules/change-completeness.mdc`. This table is the fast path; the authoritative catalog and decision tree live in `agent-os/skills/skill-index/SKILL.md` (consult it first for anything not listed here), and the file-pattern → skill map is `agent-os/docs/skill-triggers.md`.

Behaviour: infer sensible defaults from the codebase rather than asking, and run the whole matched chain. The **one** confirmation checkpoint is the new-requirement plan gate in `agent-os/rules/new-requirement-intake.mdc` ("propose a Plan once, wait for **go**"); outside that, proceed without stopping to ask.

## Task → skill

| Task pattern | Skill(s) | Path |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Any new requirement** (domain, route, schema, worker) — master orchestrator | auto-implement | `agent-os/skills/auto-implement/SKILL.md` |
| New/changed **route or endpoint** (`*.routes.ts`) | api-contract-guard → route-schema-doc-guard → route-catalog → seed-maintainer | `agent-os/skills/api-contract-guard/SKILL.md` |
| Route params, public ids, statuses, headers, list-query | api-contract-guard | `agent-os/skills/api-contract-guard/SKILL.md` |
| New/changed **schema or table** (`*.schema.ts`) | schema-generator → sql-design-guard → db-migration-maintainer → rls-tenant-isolation-guard | `agent-os/skills/schema-generator/SKILL.md` |
| SQL migration (`migrations/*.sql`) | db-migration-maintainer | `agent-os/skills/db-migration-maintainer/SKILL.md` |
| New **domain or sub-domain** scaffold | domain-generator | `agent-os/skills/domain-generator/SKILL.md` |
| **Events / queues / workers** | workers-events → test-generator | `agent-os/skills/workers-events/SKILL.md` |
| Money/state **idempotent write**, Stripe mutation, idempotency middleware | idempotency-guard | `agent-os/skills/idempotency-guard/SKILL.md` |
| RLS / tenant isolation, DB context wrappers, worker DB access | rls-tenant-isolation-guard | `agent-os/skills/rls-tenant-isolation-guard/SKILL.md` |
| **Seed** data (`seed/**`) alignment | seed-maintainer | `agent-os/skills/seed-maintainer/SKILL.md` |
| Validators, serializers, or any test layer | test-generator | `agent-os/skills/test-generator/SKILL.md` |
| User-facing copy / translation keys (`locales/**`) | i18n-message-guard | `agent-os/skills/i18n-message-guard/SKILL.md` |
| Env var add / rename / remove (`env-schema.ts`, `.env.example`) | env-schema-add | `agent-os/skills/env-schema-add/SKILL.md` |
| Public export added / renamed | tsdoc-export-guard | `agent-os/skills/tsdoc-export-guard/SKILL.md` |
| **Finishing any code change** — propagate to tests, docs, rules, skills | change-completeness-guard | `agent-os/skills/change-completeness-guard/SKILL.md` |
| About to `git commit` / fix a failed commit | before-commit-guard | `agent-os/skills/before-commit-guard/SKILL.md` |
| Dependency add/update or `pnpm audit` failure | dependency-security | `agent-os/skills/dependency-security/SKILL.md` |
| Hand-written docs under `docs/**` | docs-maintainer | `agent-os/skills/docs-maintainer/SKILL.md` |
| Directory/naming/structure changes, MCP template mirrors | structure-maintainer | `agent-os/skills/structure-maintainer/SKILL.md` |
| "Which skill applies?" / full catalog | skill-index | `agent-os/skills/skill-index/SKILL.md` |
| Broad read-heavy exploration across many files | delegate-search | `agent-os/skills/delegate-search/SKILL.md` |
| PR CI failing — diagnose one check | ci-investigator | `agent-os/skills/ci-investigator/SKILL.md` |
| Get a PR merge-ready (CI + review loop) | pr-babysit | `agent-os/skills/pr-babysit/SKILL.md` |
| Split a branch/large change into reviewable PRs | split-to-prs | `agent-os/skills/split-to-prs/SKILL.md` |

## Orchestration manifests

Ordered multi-skill chains (which skills run in sequence for a change type) live in
`agent-os/skills/chains.json`; the skill taxonomy is `agent-os/skills/groups.json`. The
generated file-pattern table in `agent-os/docs/skill-triggers.md` is the single source
for "I edited file X → run skill Y". When a row here and that table disagree, the
generated table wins — update it (and re-run `pnpm agent-os:generate`) rather than
hand-editing the generated block.
